Flutter is a tool used to build mobile apps for Android and iOS using a single codebase.

In simple words:

 With Flutter, you write code once, and it runs on both Android and iPhone.

Easy example:

Instead of making two apps (one for Android, one for iOS), Flutter lets you make one app that works on both.

Why developers use Flutter:

Saves time and effort

Fast performance

Beautiful and customizable UI

Developed by Google

One-line definition:

Flutter is a framework by Google to build mobile apps for Android and iOS using one codebase.

Flutter was launched in 2017, and it was developed by Google.
